result.execSummary:
The defendant Terry L Bayliss II was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Terry L Bayliss II is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Terry L Bayliss II was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Restitution worksheet

Victim T.L appears pro se'. Defendant Terry L Bayliss in court with attorney Jesse Jon Johansen.   State of Wisconsin is not representing the victim in this case; victim/witness coordinator attended the hearing.  Court informs parties he has reviewed all submissions.  T.L. informs the Court of additional information regarding the re-injury to his arm and the medical documentation of this re-injury.  Court explains the problems with the additional information provided; questions mileage requested, 3500 miles; tax refund for 2015 would have been approximately $8,500.00.  Atty Johansen has no further evidence for the defense; asks for a breakdown of the requested mileage.  Court informs parties crime victim services is requesting $33,000. in lost wages they have already paid to T.L.  Court incorporates restitution worksheet from the Erik Bayliss case into this case.
Atty Johansen motion to not pay because of inability to pay.  Not working currently, dealing with some medical issues and does anticipate he will be returning to work once released from this program.  Calls T.L. as a witness; T.L. sworn and questioned by Atty Johansen; Court indicates he is satisfied with evidence re: tear in shoulder muscle, C&C evidence injury required surgery and surgery occured, T.L. was out of work; mileage granted $1,400.26 (J&S w/co-actors), State of Wisc. paid T.L. for lost wages of $33,000.00 and large portion of lost wages due to the injury of this incident; however, second surgery not proven to be related to incident; satisfied by evidence presented neither defendant has the ability to pay, this is according to the law-Erik Bayliss was co-actor with Terry Bayliss II and therefore J&S liability for restitution; Court finds lost wages $20,000.00 total based on the ability to pay (J&S w/ co-actor) (State of Wisc Crime Prevention assessed $16,000. and T.L assessed $4,000.); total $21,400.26 is ordered as restitution due to T.L., informs T.L. he is free to sue in civil action.  This restitution should be included in the amended JOC for this case and the JOC for the co-actor.

Defendant Terry L Bayliss in court with attorney Jesse Jon Johansen.   Victim T.L. appears representing himself.  One restitution held on companion case in which decision has not been rendered yet.  Significant testimony in that case.  Court questions T.L. if he has any more substantive testimony or if he wanted to add to what was already submitted.  T.L. wishes to add to his testimony from last hearing.  Sworn and testifies.  Injury to bicep was three days after surgery.  Defendant submits documents to court supporting his testimony.  Court reviews.  Atty. Johansen motions to adjourn based on the records submitted by T.L.  Would like a couple of weeks to consult with a physician regarding medical records.  T.L. argument.  Court - will let Johansen have time to review  the documents.  CD submitted with photos received.  Clerk to print color copies and mail them to Atty. Johansen.  Restitution hearing scheduled for June 7, 2017 at 03:00 pm.
